Keyano [phonetic] Taiko.

00:09:03.530 --> 00:09:07.060
We started San Jose Taiko
in 1973, so it was around

00:09:07.060 --> 00:09:13.080
and that really it's connecting
to the ideas around 1972, 1973 on.

00:09:13.080 --> 00:09:14.380
&gt;&gt; Daniel Sheehy: Great.

00:09:14.380 --> 00:09:15.680
Thanks. PJ?

00:09:15.680 --> 00:09:18.120
&gt;&gt; PJ Hirabayashi: Ditto.

00:09:18.120 --> 00:09:24.770
[Laugh] Just to kind of cap on our
similarities, my grandparents are

00:09:24.770 --> 00:09:32.150 position:56%
from Japan, and my parents were born
in California, and I grew up in,

00:09:32.150 --> 00:09:34.030
well, I was born in 1950, so right

00:09:34.030 --> 00:09:37.720
after World War II, I
went to public school.

00:09:37.720 --> 00:09:47.210
That was 1955-ish, and I was
the only Asian face at school,

00:09:47.210 --> 00:09:50.900
and I was quickly reminded
that I was already different.

00:09:50.900 --> 00:09:54.730
And there was something about going
to school and already being cast

00:09:54.730 --> 00:09:58.490
out as being different and not
included and the separation

00:09:58.490 --> 00:10:01.350 position:56%
