00:10:01.350 --> 00:10:06.550
So, there was already this very
seething feeling of inferiority,

00:10:06.550 --> 00:10:11.590
less than, no self-esteem, and
that's how I actually felt,

00:10:11.590 --> 00:10:17.090
you know, not being included
for a long period of time.

00:10:17.090 --> 00:10:21.800
And so, just kind of quickly
forward, to have heard Taiko

00:10:21.800 --> 00:10:27.490
in the early 1970's, all of
a sudden became like "Wow!"

00:10:27.490 --> 00:10:33.120 position:56%
I saw this energy, you know, and
they were, there were men and women.

00:10:33.120 --> 00:10:35.530
They were all dressed
up in happi coat,

00:10:35.530 --> 00:10:36.830
and in San Francisco [inaudible].

00:10:36.830 --> 00:10:44.010
By the way, Sage Tanaka is
also a Heritage Fellow too.

00:10:44.010 --> 00:10:52.560 position:56%
And to be able to see this unabashed
energy coming from the stage,

00:10:52.560 --> 00:10:57.630
this expression, and immediately
it's like I want to do that;

00:10:57.630 --> 00:10:59.640
almost like, I can do that.

00:10:59.640 --> 00:11:01.710
How can I do that?

00:11:01.710 --> 00:11:07.770
And so it was like that exploration
of, okay, I want to find Taiko,

00:11:07.770 --> 00:11:10.120
how I could become like this.

00:11:10.120 --> 00:11:14.930
I always use the word "ballistic,"
you know, being a woman too,

00:11:14.930 --> 00:11:21.730
it's like you're always, and Asian
woman too, so ballistic was like,

00:11:21.730 --> 00:11:26.380
