started from Japan towns.

00:31:29.550 --> 00:31:32.600
Three Japantowns who made
it in the United States

00:31:32.600 --> 00:31:36.530
that are physical entities still
and recognized as Japantowns,

00:31:36.530 --> 00:31:40.290
Los Angeles and San
Francisco and San Jose.

00:31:40.290 --> 00:31:45.100
So, in that way, we see
like how important it became

00:31:45.100 --> 00:31:49.720
as a pioneer voice for these
communities that, you know,

00:31:49.720 --> 00:31:54.250
it's like, oh, I'd like to learn
more, you know, and it's like also,

00:31:54.250 --> 00:31:56.920
hey, there's this celebration,
you know,

00:31:56.920 --> 00:31:59.300
this is happening in Japantown.

00:31:59.300 --> 00:32:00.600
Come on out.

00:32:00.600 --> 00:32:03.070
And so there's also
this awareness building

00:32:03.070 --> 00:32:06.720
of what the community
is and the larger city.

00:32:06.720 --> 00:32:10.550
And then, also, we always
